INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (89, 1, '2009-03-05 06:37:27', '2009-03-05 14:37:27', '[caption id="attachment_82" align="alignnone" width="400" caption="Sierra HR Partners Inc."]<img class="size-full wp-image-82" title="group" src="http://localhost:8080/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/group.jpg" alt="Sierra HR Partners Inc." width="400" height="188" />[/caption]\r\n\r\n<h3>Brenda G. Budke</h3>\r\n\r\nBrenda G. Budke is a Certified Senior Professional in Human Resources (SPHR) with over 20 years experience in the human resource field. Prior to joining Sierra HR Partners, Brenda served as Human Resources Manager for a communications company with 850 employees, overseeing employment, employee relations and training. She is founder and dean of a corporate university and has developed curriculum and presented performance based training at all levels. Ms. Budke holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Organizational Behavior with a concentration in Human Resource Management from the University of San Francisco.\r\n\r\nHer specialized training certifications include: Covey’s 7-Habits of Highly Effective People; Franklin Covey’s “What Matters Most” time management; all core communication and performance improvement modules of Achieve Global’s Frontline Leadership; and the Newspaper Association of America (NAA) Diversity Awareness program.\r\n\r\nMs. Budke is a current board member and past president of the Central California Employment Round Table working in conjunction with DFEH to prevent discrimination in the workplace; Vice President of the Human Resource Association of Central California (HRACC), a Fresno Rotarian, and member of the Society of\r\nHuman Resource Management (SHRM).\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Victorine Goosev</h3>\r\n\r\nVictorine Goosev is a California State University, Fresno Alumnus with a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration, Human Resource Management. In addition, she has extensive training in Occupational Safety and Health compliance.   During her tenure at Fresno State, Ms. Goosev was highly active in the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM) Student and National chapters.  She served on the student executive board as the secretary and helped the chapter receive the national honor of “Top 10 Student Chapter Merit Award” for two consecutive years.  Ms. Goosev has passed the intensive exam for Professional in Human Resources (PHR) and is currently working toward the requirements for full certification.\r\n\r\nMs. Goosev’s Human Resources and compliance training includes:  Behavioral Interviews, Career Development Series: Sexual Harassment Series - AB1825, HR Hero Line:  Overtime Regulations, Achieving Higher Customer Service Standards, Legal Aspects of Human Resource Management, Administration of Personnel, Compensation Strategies, and Staffing an Organization.\r\n\r\nMs. Goosev’s experience and work includes preparation of Injury Illness and Prevention Programs (IIPP), Emergency Evacuation Programs and development of employee policies and practices such as Paid Family Leave.  Prior to joining Sierra HR Partners, Victorine worked in the legal and training fields.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Paris Boone</h3>\r\n\r\nParis Boone is a human resources professional with over nine years experience in training and development. He received a Bachelor of Science degree from Brigham Young University.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Sierra HR Partners, Mr. Boone served as Director of Operations and Human Resources Manager for a company in Florida. He was responsible for increasing supervisor and employee effectiveness through training and coaching programs, including building systems and processes to streamline workflow and increase company profits.\r\n\r\nMr. Boone has substantial experience in employee relations, including mediating employee disputes and resolving grievances. He has also developed supervisor and employee training programs to improve job effectiveness and prevent unlawful harassment. He also assists employers with drafting employee handbooks and job descriptions, and conducting effective employee evaluations. Mr. Boone is a member of the Society for Human Resource Management. He and his wife Kasey, a Clovis native, recently returned to the area with their three children.', 'Our Team', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-4', '', '', '2009-03-05 06:37:27', '2009-03-05 14:37:27', '', 31, 'http://sierrahr.com/2009/03/31-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
