rom Brigham Young University.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Sierra HR Partners, Mr. Boone served as Director of Operations and Human Resources Manager for a company in Florida. He was responsible for increasing supervisor and employee effectiveness through training and coaching programs, including building systems and processes to streamline workflow and increase company profits.\r\n\r\nMr. Boone has substantial experience in employee relations,including mediating employee disputes and resolving grievances. He has also developed supervisor and employee training programs to improve job effectiveness and prevent unlawful harassment. He also assists employers with drafting employee handbooks and job descriptions, and conducting effective employee evaluations. Mr. Boone is a member of the Society for Human Resource Management. He and his wife Kasey, a Clovis native, recently returned to the area with their three children.\r\n<h3><hr /><a rel="attachment wp-att-437" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/bio-pic-2/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-437" title="Bio Pic" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/Bio-Pic1-150x150.jpg" alt="Bio Pic" width="150" height="150" /></a>Laura Martina</h3>\r\nHR Consultant\r\n\r\nLaura Martina is a Certified Professional in Human Resources (PHR) with over 7 years of experience developing and implementing HR and business policies. Ms. Martina earned her Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in Human Resource Management from California State University, Fresno.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Sierra HR Partners, Laura served as Human Resource Director for a local financial institution. As a strategic member of management, she is experienced in facilitating collaboration among management and staff to enhance performance and ensure compliance with all regulations.\r\n\r\nMs. Martina has wide-ranging HR experience including coaching, counseling, employee motivation, recruitment, improving retention, teamwork, customer service, and overall best business practices. As an entrepreneur, Laura believes that success is looking at the big picture and building the relationships to support it. She and her husband Jason, live in the Oakhurst area with their two children.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a rel="attachment wp-att-182" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/s_martirosyan-copy/"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-182" title="S_Martirosyan copy" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/S_Martirosyan-copy.jpg" alt="S_Martirosyan copy" width="111" height="157" /></a>Suzy Martirosyan</h3>\r\nHR Associate\r\n\r\nSuzy Martirosyan graduated summa cum laude from California State University, Fresno with a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration and an emphasis in Human Resource Management. She passed the Professional in Human Resources (PHR) exam upon graduation and became certified in June 2009. Suzy and her teammates participated in the 2008 Pacific West Regional HR Games Competition in Long Beach, CA and received the first place honor.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a rel="attachment wp-att-484" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/nancy-vang-4/"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-497" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/nancy-vang-6/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-497" title="Nancy Vang" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/Nancy-Vang5-107x150.jpg" alt="Nancy Vang" width="107" height="150" /></a> Nancy Vang</h3>\r\nHR Associate\r\n\r\nNancy Vang is a graduate of California State University, Fresno.  She earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in Human Resource Management and a certificate in Cross-Cultural Competency. Upon graduation, she is an active member of the national chapter of the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM). Nancy is the Background Investigation Specialist with experience in criminal and civil records searches, DMV history reports, credit history reports, educational history verifications, employment &amp; business reference verifications, professional license verifications, and social security number verifications. \r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a rel="attachment wp-att-489" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/lauren-stefanopoulos/"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-498" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/lauren-stefanopoulos-2/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-498" title="Lauren Stefanopoulos" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/Lauren-Stefanopoulos1-107x150.jpg" alt="Lauren Stefanopoulos" width="107" height="150" /></a>Lauren Stefanopoulos </h3>\r\nReceptionist/Administrative Assistant\r\n\r\nLauren Stefanopoulos graduated from California State University, Fresno with a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in Human Resource Management.', 'Our Team', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-69', '', '', '2011-11-30 10:01:33', '2011-11-30 18:01:33', '', 31, 'http://sierrahr.com/2011/11/31-revision-69/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
