INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (750, 1, '2014-02-27 12:30:23', '2014-02-27 20:30:23', '<h3><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-86" title="budke" src="http://localhost:8080/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/budke.jpg" alt="budke" width="117" height="125" /></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Brenda G. Budke</h3>\r\nExecutive Director\r\n\r\nBrenda G. Budke is a Certified Senior Professional in Human Resources (SPHR) with over 20 years experience in the human resource field. Prior to joining Sierra HR Partners, Brenda served as Human Resources Manager for a communications company with 850 employees, overseeing employment, employee relations and training. She is founder and dean of a corporate university and has developed curriculum and presented performance based training at all levels. Ms. Budke holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Organizational Behavior with a concentration in Human Resource Management from the University of San Francisco.\r\n\r\nHer specialized training certifications include: Covey’s 7-Habits of Highly Effective People; Franklin Covey’s “What Matters Most” time management; all core communication and performance improvement modules of Achieve Global’s Frontline Leadership; and the Newspaper Association of America (NAA) Diversity Awareness program.\r\n\r\nMs. Budke is a current board member and past president of the Central California Employment Round Table working in conjunction with DFEH to prevent discrimination in the workplace; Vice President of the Human Resource Association of Central California (HRACC), a Fresno Rotarian, and member of the Society of Human Resource Management (SHRM).\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a rel="attachment wp-att-182" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/s_martirosyan-copy/"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-182" title="S_Martirosyan copy" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/S_Martirosyan-copy.jpg" alt="S_Martirosyan copy" width="111" height="157" /></a>Suzy Martirosyan</h3>\r\nHR Associate\r\n\r\nSuzy Martirosyan graduated summa cum laude from California State University, Fresno with a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration and an emphasis in Human Resource Management. She passed the Professional in Human Resources (PHR) exam upon graduation and became certified in June 2009. Suzy and her teammates participated in the 2008 Pacific West Regional HR Games Competition in Long Beach, CA and received the first place honor.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a rel="attachment wp-att-484" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/nancy-vang-4/"></a><a rel="attachment wp-att-497" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/nancy-vang-6/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-497" title="Nancy Vang" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/Nancy-Vang5-107x150.jpg" alt="Nancy Vang" width="107" height="150" /></a>Nancy Vang</h3>\r\nHR Associate\r\n\r\nNancy Vang is a graduate of California State University, Fresno.  She earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in Human Resource Management and a certificate in Cross-Cultural Competency. Upon graduation, she is an active member of the national chapter of the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM). Nancy is the Background Investigation Specialist with experience in criminal and civil records searches, DMV history reports, credit history reports, educational history verifications, employment &amp; business reference verifications, professional license verifications, and social security number verifications.\r\n<h3><a rel="attachment wp-att-691" href="http://sierrahr.com/our-team/janet-keene-387/"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-691" title="Janet Keene 387" src="http://sierrahr.com/wp-content/uploads/Janet-Keene-387-150x150.jpg" alt="Janet Keene 387" width="150" height="150" /></a>Janet Keene</h3>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: normal;">Consultant</span>\r\n\r\nJanet Keene is a Certified Professional in Human Resources (PHR).  She earned her Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with an emphasis in the Legal Environment of Business from California State University, Fresno.  She has worked in the Human Resources profession for over 14 years and has hands-on experience in recruitment, training, performance management, compensation and benefits, and ensuring HR effectiveness during periods of significant organizational change.\r\n<h3>Korinna Pedrosa</h3>\r\nConsultant\r\n\r\nKorinna is a Certified Professional in Human Resources (PHR) with over 10 years of human resources and business experience in a variety of industries. Prior to joining Sierra HR Partners, Pedrosa served as Talent Acquisition Manager for a large, non-profit community action agency with 1,200 employees, responsible for managing high volume recruitment, hiring and onboarding plus auxiliary support with employee relations, training, compensation, career development and performance management functions.  She holds a master’s degree in business administration (MBA) and bachelor’s degree (BA) in Mass Communication and Journalism.\r\n\r\nKorinna serves on the board of Central California SHRM/HRACC, a member of the Society of Human Resource Management (SHRM) and is an active member of the community. A lifelong resident of the Central Valley, she is passionate about continual learning, serving the needs of others, and running.', ' Our Team', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '31-revision-123', '', '', '2014-02-27 12:30:23', '2014-02-27 20:30:23', '', 31, 'http://sierrahr.com/2014/02/31-revision-123/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
